PATIENUGU – United States Consulate, Lagos in collaboration with Godfrey Okoye University Enugu has trained over 200 secondary school students and teachers on DNA Barcoding as part of its commitment to support the development of STEM research in Nigeria. Speaking at the Closing Ceremony of the United States government-sponsored Back To Science Initiative implemented by the DNA learning Center, Godfrey Okoye University, Enugu. Steven Ibeli, Public Affairs Officer, US Consulate General in Lagos said “We are here to celebrate a milestone in Enugu which is the US policy of promoting Science, Technology Education in Nigeria. “We funded the organization called the DNA lab with Godfrey Okoye University to bring practical science education training to Enugu through the study of DNA because we don’t want the students to have only theoretical knowledge but real practical knowledge. “There are over 160 secondary school students who benefited from this training and we also train 42 teachers to also train their students who are future leaders.